Gene ID Conversion.

IDConversion.Rd

Gene ID Conversion.

IDConversion(
  deres,
  gene.type = c("ENSEMBL", "ENTREZID", "SYMBOL"),
  org.db = "org.Mm.eg.db",
  gene.map = NULL,
  sort.key = "log2FoldChange"
)

Arguments

deres

Data frame contains all genes.
gene.type

Gene name type. Chosen from ENSEMBL, ENTREZID, SYMBOL. Default: ENSEMBL.
org.db

Organism database. Default: org.Mm.eg.db.
gene.map

Use data frame instead of org.db to conduct gene id conversion, first column should be Gene. Default: NULL.
sort.key

Column to sort the results. Default: log2FoldChange.

Value

Data frame contains gene id conversion results.

Examples

library(DEbPeak)
count.file <- system.file("extdata", "snon_count.txt", package = "DEbPeak")
count.matrix <- read.table(file = count.file, header = TRUE, sep = "\t")
IDConversion(count.matrix, gene.type = "ENSEMBL", sort.key = NULL)
